The paper discusses multimedia retrieval, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). It specifically focuses on cross-media retrieval, which involves different media types, such as text, image, video, audio, and 3D models. This makes it relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG) as well. Additionally, the paper mentions benchmarks and datasets, which are often used in multimedia research (cs.MM).
